<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Absolutely positioned, non-replaced elements, vertical centering</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#abs-replaced-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify that an element is vertically centered and both 'margin-top' and 'margin-botton' get equal values, when 'top', 'bottom' and 'height' are all are not auto and 'margin-top' and 'margin-bottom' are both 'auto'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                position: relative;
                border: 3px solid black;
                height: 3in;
                width: 3in;
            }
            #d2
            {
                position: absolute;
                top: 1in;
                bottom: 1in;
                height: 1in;
                margin-top: auto;
                margin-bottom: auto;
                background: blue;
                width: 3in;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the blue box is vertically centered in the black bordered box.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div id="d2"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>